<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Ring of the Shissar</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Ring of the Shissar">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
MAGIC 
LORE 
NO DROP 



<br><br>


<b>Inventory Slots:</b> Fingers
<br>







<b>Armor Class:</b> 8<br>
<b>Modifiers:</b> Sta +4, Wis +4, Int +4, HP +80, Mana +65<br>
<b>Size:</b> Tiny<br>
<b>Weight:</b> 0.1<br>

<br>
<b>Classes:</b> ALL<br>
<b>Races:</b> ALL<br>

<b>Effect Type:</b> Permanent<br>


<br>

<b>Description:</b> <br>This ring is the key to the Emperor/Blood areas of Ssraeshza. You obtain it by combining 3 other items from the zone together.<br><br>



<table width="300" bgcolor="#004b97"><b><font color=#d2d200>Effect: 
<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=spellsbrdcomplete&eqspells.spell_name=%22Improved%20Healing%20III%22">Improved Healing III</a></b></font></table><br>








<b>Duration:</b> 3 Minutes<br>
<br><b>Description:</b> 1: Focus Attribute: 7D (20)<BR>2: Restriction: Spells level 60 and lower<BR>3: Restriction: Only applies to 'Hit Points (HP)' spells<BR>4: Restriction: Affects 'Instant' spells only<BR>5: Restriction: 'Beneficial' spells only<BR>6: Restriction: Exclude spell 'Complete Healing'<BR>7: Restriction: Exclude spell 'Complete Heal'<br>












<br><table width="300" bgcolor="#004b97"><b><font color=#d2d200>Obtained in 
<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqquestfull&eqquests.quest_name=%22Emperor%20Ssraeshza%20Key%22">Emperor Ssraeshza Key</a> Quest</b></font></table><br>
<b>Recommended Level:</b> 60<br>
<b>Starting NPC:</b> <br><br>

<b>Description</b>:<br>
This is the quest to create the ring that acts as a key to Emperor Ssraeshza's chamber.<BR><BR>This spoiler is given in a no nonsense fashion.<BR><BR>1) Go to the basement level of the Shissar temple.<BR><BR>2) Kill any of the named Taskmasters that can be used to trigger the Glyphed/Exiled/Cursed fights.  The Taskmasters frequently drop the pouch necessary to combine the items.<BR><BR>3) Once you have acquired the pouch.  Head to the first floor and camp the random rare spawn Commander Zazuzh.  He drops the idol you need.<BR><BR>4) Once you've acquired the idol, go to the second floor and in similiar fashion camp the random rare spawn Commander Zeruzsh.  He drops the ring you need.<BR><BR>5) Then head to the Imperial Guard chamber where you can access the locked teleport to the Emperor's chamber.  By killing the Imperial Guards you can spawn 3 named rares all of which drop the last piece you need, the insignia.  These are General Kizuhx, Arbiter Korazhk, and Advisor Zekuzh.<BR><BR>6) Put all 3 items into the pouch and combine.  You will receive a <b>Ring of the Shissar</b>.<br>


<br><table width="300" bgcolor="#004b97"><b><font color=#d2d200>Found in <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqzone&eqzones.zone_name=%22Ssraeashza%20Temple%22">Ssraeashza Temple</a></b></font></table><br>
<b>Continent:</b> Luclin<br>
<b>Zone Type:</b> Dungeon<br>
<b>Level Ranges:</b> 50 - 60<br>
<b>Connects To:</b> The Deep, The Grey<br><br>

<b>Description:</b><br>This temple is the last remaining evidence of the SSraeashza Empire -- the race which inslaved the Iksar on Kunark in ages past.  This is an extremely high level zone with at least 5 levels.  To reach the 5th level a key is required that consists of a container and 3 parts which are dropped on the other 4 floors.  Both single parties and raids can be effective here.<br>


